---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="What is pH?" description="Learn what pH means, how the pH scale works, and the difference between acids and bases">
  <style>
    .article-header { background: #712B13; border-radius: 12px; padding: 2rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
    .tags { display: flex; gap: 8px; margin-bottom: 12px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
    .tag { font-size: 11px; padding: 3px 10px; border-radius: 999px; font-weight: 500; }
    .article-title { font-size: 28px; font-weight: 600; color: #FAECE7; line-height: 1.3; margin-bottom: 10px; }
    .objective { background: #993C1D; border-radius: 8px; padding: 0.75rem 1rem; font-size: 14px; color: #FAECE7; }
    .objective strong { color: #FAC775; }
    .vocab-box { background: #FAECE7; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
    .vocab-title { font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; color: #712B13; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; margin-bottom: 12px; }
    .vocab-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr)); gap: 10px; }
    .vocab-item { background: white; border-radius: 8px; padding: 0.75rem 1rem; }
    .vocab-word { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; color: #712B13; margin-bottom: 3px; }
    .vocab-def { font-size: 13px; color: #555; line-height: 1.5; }
    .video-link { display: block; background: #1a1a2e; border-radius: 12px; padding: 2rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; text-decoration: none; text-align: center; }
    .video-icon { font-size: 32px; margin-bottom: 8px; }
    .video-title { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 600; color: #EEEDFE; margin-bottom: 6px; }
    .video-subtitle { font-size: 13px; color: #AFA9EC; }
    .facts-box { background: #f5f5f5; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
    .facts-title { font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; color: #712B13; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; margin-bottom: 12px; }
    .fact { display: flex; gap: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; align-items: flex-start; }
    .fact-dot { width: 8px; height: 8px; border-radius: 50%; background: #712B13; flex-shrink: 0; margin-top: 6px; }
    .fact-text { font-size: 15px; color: #1a1a2e; line-height: 1.6; }
    .fact-text strong { color: #712B13; }
    .summary-box { background: #712B13; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
    .summary-title { font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; color: #FAC775; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; margin-bottom: 10px; }
    .summary-text { font-size: 15px; color: #FAECE7; line-height: 1.7; }
    .topic-tags { display: flex; gap: 8px; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-top: 2rem; }
    .topic-tag { font-size: 12px; padding: 5px 12px; border-radius: 999px; }
  </style>

  <div class="article-header">
    <div class="tags">
      <span class="tag" style="background:#FAECE7;color:#712B13;">General</span>
      <span class="tag" style="background:#FAECE7;color:#712B13;">Acids & Bases</span>
    </div>
    <h1 class="article-title">What is pH?</h1>
    <div class="objective"><strong>Learning objective:</strong> Explain what pH measures and describe the difference between acids, bases and neutral substances.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="vocab-box">
    <div class="vocab-title">Key vocabulary</div>
    <div class="vocab-grid">
      <div class="vocab-item">
        <div class="vocab-word">pH</div>
        <div class="vocab-def">A scale from 0 to 14 that measures how acidic or basic a solution is. Lower numbers are more acidic.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="vocab-item">
        <div class="vocab-word">Acid</div>
        <div class="vocab-def">A substance with a pH below 7. Acids release hydrogen ions (H⁺) in water.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="vocab-item">
        <div class="vocab-word">Base</div>
        <div class="vocab-def">A substance with a pH above 7. Bases release hydroxide ions (OH⁻) in water.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="vocab-item">
        <div class="vocab-word">Neutral</div>
        <div class="vocab-def">A substance with a pH of exactly 7. Pure water is neutral.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="vocab-item">
        <div class="vocab-word">Neutralization</div>
        <div class="vocab-def">A reaction between an acid and a base that produces water and a salt.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="vocab-item">
        <div class="vocab-word">Indicator</div>
        <div class="vocab-def">A substance that changes color depending on whether a solution is acidic or basic.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <a href="https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=pH+scale+acids+and+bases+high+school+chemistry" target="_blank" class="video-link">
    <div class="video-icon">▶</div>
    <div class="video-title">Watch on YouTube</div>
    <div class="video-subtitle">Search: pH scale acids and bases high school chemistry</div>
  </a>

  <div class="facts-box">
    <div class="facts-title">Key facts</div>
    <div class="fact">
      <div class="fact-dot"></div>
      <div class="fact-text">The <strong>pH scale</strong> runs from 0 to 14. A pH below 7 is acidic, above 7 is basic, and exactly 7 is neutral.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="fact">
      <div class="fact-dot"></div>
      <div class="fact-text">Common acids include lemon juice (pH 2), vinegar (pH 3), and stomach acid (pH 1-2). Common bases include baking soda (pH 9) and bleach (pH 13).</div>
    </div>
    <div class="fact">
      <div class="fact-dot"></div>
      <div class="fact-text">The pH scale is <strong>logarithmic</strong> — each step is 10 times more acidic or basic than the one before. pH 4 is 10 times more acidic than pH 5.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="fact">
      <div class="fact-dot"></div>
      <div class="fact-text">When an acid and a base react together the result is <strong>neutralization</strong> — they cancel each other out to form water and a salt.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="fact">
      <div class="fact-dot"></div>
      <div class="fact-text"><strong>Indicators</strong> like litmus paper change color in acidic or basic solutions. Red litmus turns blue in a base, blue litmus turns red in an acid.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="summary-box">
    <div class="summary-title">Summary</div>
    <div class="summary-text">
      pH is a scale from 0 to 14 that measures how acidic or basic a solution is. Acids have a pH below 7 and release hydrogen ions, while bases have a pH above 7 and release hydroxide ions. When an acid and base react they neutralize each other producing water and a salt.
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="topic-tags">
    <span class="topic-tag" style="background:#FAECE7;color:#712B13;">Acids & Bases</span>
    <span class="topic-tag" style="background:#FAEEDA;color:#633806;">General</span>
    <span class="topic-tag" style="background:#EEEDFE;color:#534AB7;">pH scale</span>
    <span class="topic-tag" style="background:#E1F5EE;color:#085041;">Neutralization</span>
  </div>
</Layout>